Agrostis gigantea

   [2937.jpg]
    Authority   Roth.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms   Agrostis nigra
   Common names black bentgrass, agrostide grande
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2937

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A rhizomatous grass with an open panicle, slightly
   red in appearance, and with relatively broad leaves reaching a height
   of up to 60-120 cm. USES Grown for pasture. GROWING PERIOD Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES Common bentgrass, Redtop. FURTHER INF: It is native to
   temperate and cold areas of the northern hemisphere (Europe). It has a
   large climate range and good resistance to cold and good
   drought-resistance. Optimum on excessively drained, relatively dry
   sods. Thrives on moderately rich to nutrient rich soils. Mainly on
   light, sandy soils. It is usually regarded as a weed.

   Sources
